news.title: RLDA to lease land parcel in Ludhiana at Rs 108 crore
news.para: The area of the site spans across 25,257.67 square metre while the area to be leased is around 21185.54 square metre. The proposed site has excellent connectivity to the major transportation centers of the city.

news.title: Hyderabad: 2BHK projects lack access to basic services
news.para: In the pilot assessment of the affordable housing schemes carried out by the CSE, it was also pointed out that there is still considerable scope of reducing heat gain in buildings, improving ventilation and day-lit areas to improve thermal comfort and reduce energy intensity of structures.

news.title: Emami Realty surges 10% on CARE's rating upgrade
news.para: Speaking about the prospects of the realty sector in West Bengal, Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer Nitesh Kumar, earlier this month, expressed optimism, saying that the extension of the window for stamp duty reduction had benefited the real estate environment on the whole.

news.title: SICMA requests FM to facilitate movement of cement from southern states to deficit regions
news.para: South India, with 180 Million Tonnes Per Annum (MPTA) capacity accounts for almost 40 per cent of the India's cement production and 35-40 per cent of limestone was also found in the southern parts of the country.

news.title: Office leasing to grow by 30–35% in 2022 : Experts
news.para: “Overall, we estimate net absorption to rebound strongly, recording a 30–35% growth to reach 29–31 million square feet (msf) levels by the end of 2022, in line with the decadal average,” said Badal Yagnik, managing director - tenant representation, Cushman & Wakefield. “Overall, the office story is looking very promising in the year ahead.”

news.title: Stuck registries of flats in Noida may inflate EMI for homebuyers
news.para: The bank notices have cited delay in registry of flats as the reason. They have referred to certain conditions mentioned in the sanction letter that was signed between the buyer and the bank during the disbursement of home loans.

news.title: NCLT directs Indiabulls Real Estate to discuss Embassy merger with shareholders
news.para: This is the last hurdle to be cleared by the company for the proposed merger that would result in Indiabulls Group’s complete exit from real estate business and a reverse listing for Embassy.

news.title: China's top real estate regulator vows to tackle property delivery risks: Xinhua
news.para: Wang Menghui, head of the Ministry of Housing and Urban-Rural Development, also told Xinhua that China will keep its real estate policies consistent and stable, while strengthening coordination in areas including finance, and land and market supervision.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh CM lays foundation stones of Indore metro
news.para: The foundation stone for the first phase of the 31.55-kilometre-long Indore's metro rail project, estimated to cost Rs 7,500.80 crore, was laid by then CM Kamal Nath on September 14, 2019.

news.title: Chennai: Metro in suburbs on fast-track
news.para: “We have set a 2025 deadline for Power House to Poonamallee stretch (corridor 4). In a few months, other elevated stretches will also be ready. We are pushing for the deadline, but it depends on the contractor,” an official said.

news.title: China's central bank says to promote healthy development of property market
news.para: The statement from the People's Bank of China (PBOC), made following its fourth-quarter monetary policy committee meeting, is the latest sign that Chinese regulators are marginally easing curbs on the property sector to prevent a hard-landing.

news.title: WeWork India revenue up 33% at Rs 800 crore in 2021
news.para: Looking at the growing demand for flexibility, Karan Virwani, CEO, WeWork India said the company would expand its portfolio by one million square feet area with capacity of about 20,000 desks.

news.title: Jaipur development body to fix use of greenfield airport land
news.para: After the decision was taken that airport will not be constructed on the reserved land, the town planning wing has started the exercise to earmark the area as ‘special area’ in the Master Plan 2025. The notification for the same will be released soon.

news.title: Mumbai: Producer remanded to judicial custody in Rs 13.7 crore housing fraud
news.para: Jain was arrested by the Economic Offences Wing (EOW) in 2016 for allegedly cheating home buyers; later, multiple FIRs were registered against him and his company.

news.title: Mumbai: Tenants, landlords unite to redevelop Kamathipura
news.para: For the 800 landlords and over 8,000 tenants of Kamathipura, who have waited years for their properties to be redeveloped, hope is finally on the horizon.
